cui_name: Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor, Not Otherwise Specified
parent_disease: Embryonal Tumors of the Nervous System
reasoning: CNS embryonal tumors (including medulloblastoma, PNET, and other malignant embryonal tumors) are rare pediatric malignancies. Reported as incidence (new cases per year). Global incidence approximately 0.4-0.5 per 100k population, with higher rates in children. Confidence limited by heterogeneous grouping under 'NOS' designation and variable histological classification across regions.
